\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\f0\fs32 Technical Specification Document (TSD)\par
\b0\fs22 Project: Multichannel Queue Management System\par
Version: 1.0\par
\par
\b\fs28 1. Introduction & Project Overview\par
\b0\fs22 This document outlines the technical specifications for the Queue Management System (QMS). This system organizes the flow of customers across one or multiple branches via interactive kiosks, public display screens, and management interfaces for agents and administrators.\par
\par
\b\fs24 1.1 Objectives\par
\b0\fs22 - Digitize and streamline ticket issuance and customer distribution.\par
- Offer a multi-branch solution managed centrally.\par
- Allow per-branch customization (services, sub-services, priorities, themes).\par
- Provide immediate visual and vocal feedback (Text-To-Speech) in waiting rooms.\par
- Ensure ticket traceability and collect customer satisfaction metrics.\par
\par
\b\fs28 2. Overall Architecture\par
\b0\fs22 The project relies on a modern Single Page Application (SPA) architecture coupled with a real-time Backend-as-a-Service (BaaS).\par
\par
\b\fs24 2.1 Software Components\par
\b0\fs22 - Frontend: React 19 application managed by Vite.\par
- Language: TypeScript for strict static typing.\par
- UI & Routing: React Router DOM for navigation. Native/Utility CSS for styling.\par
- Backend & Database: Self-hosted Supabase instance (PostgreSQL 15+) deployed via Docker Compose.\par
- Authentication: GoTrue (Supabase module) coupled with a PostgreSQL public.users profile table.\par
- Real-Time: Supabase Realtime (WebSocket subscriptions) enabling dynamic ticket updates.\par
\par
\b\fs28 3. Data Model (Database)\par
\b0\fs22 The relational database is the core of the system. It manages branch configurations, access rights, service taxonomy, and the volatile state of tickets.\par
\par
\b\fs24 3.1 Key Tables Explanation\par
\b0\fs22 - agence: Represents a physical entity containing booths (guichet) and kiosks.\par
- guichet: Represents a physical processing desk/booth. Associated with one or more service entries.\par
- service and sous_service: Categorizes the reasons for a customer's visit.\par
- active_guichets: A session table indicating which agent (user_id) is currently assigned to which guichet.\par
- ticket: A temporal entity updated in real-time (Statuses: waiting -> called -> done/cancelled).\par
- evaluations: Customer satisfaction rating collected at the end of the process.\par
\par
\b\fs28 4. Security & Access Rights\par
\b0\fs22 The system strictly enforces Row Level Security (RLS) directly within PostgreSQL to isolate data.\par
\par
\b\fs24 4.1 Roles\par
\b0\fs22 1. super_admin: Global access. Creates branches, manages all administrators, and adds global services.\par
2. admin: Manages a specific branch. Creates agents, assigns services to booths.\par
3. user (Agent): Only accesses the booth interface for their designated branch.\par
\par
\b\fs28 5. Functional Modules (Workflows)\par
\par
\b\fs24 5.1 Interactive Kiosk (Kiosk)\par
\b0\fs22 - Usage: Runs on a tablet. Access restricted by a local password.\par
- Workflow: Select main service -> Select sub-service -> Priority -> Ticket creation -> Print.\par
\par
\b\fs24 5.2 Public Display Screen (Queue Dashboard)\par
\b0\fs22 - Usage: Smart TV or Mini-PC connected to a screen.\par
- Functionality: Highlights the most recently called ticket. Uses window.speechSynthesis API to vocally announce it.\par
\par
\b\fs24 5.3 Agent Dashboard (Guichet)\par
\b0\fs22 - The agent opens a booth at the start of their session.\par
- Dynamic display of their waiting list.\par
- Available actions: Call Next, Recall, Done, or Cancel.\par
\par
\b\fs28 6. Recommended Hardware Configuration\par
\b0\fs22 Since the system is an SPA web application, it requires very few hardware resources but demands modern browsers.\par
\par
\b\fs24 6.1 Server (Self-hosted Supabase Backend)\par
\b0\fs22 - Type: VPS or Cloud Server.\par
- OS: Linux (Ubuntu 22.04 LTS recommended).\par
- Requirements: Docker and Docker Compose, at least 4 GB RAM, 40 GB SSD.\par
\par
\b\fs24 6.2 Ticket Issuance Terminal (Kiosk)\par
\b0\fs22 - Hardware: Touch tablet (iPad or Galaxy Tab) or a Windows touch terminal.\par
- Software: Kiosk Mode enabled.\par
\par
\b\fs24 6.3 Ticket Printing\par
\b0\fs22 - Hardware: Networked thermal printer (Ethernet or Wi-Fi) supporting ESC/POS.\par
\par
\b\fs24 6.4 Display Screen (Queue Dashboard)\par
\b0\fs22 - Hardware: Smart TV or a standard TV powered by a mini PC. Must be connected to speakers for audio announcements.\par
}
